OL,6,FNew policies on phones will be
OL,7,Fintroduced at eight of the trust's 32
OL,8,Fsecondary schools this term, the
OL,9,Fnewspaper reported, with the remaining
OL,10,Facademies following after liaising
OL,11,Fwith parents.
OL,13,FThe trust runs 42 establishments in
OL,14,FEngland with 35,000 pupils. Access to
OL,15,Fphones is already ruled out at the
OL,16,Ftrust's primary, special needs and
OL,17,Falternative provision schools.
